{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7834ad57-c1ad-40f7-8d48-976869e61c24","content":"In .NET MAUI, you configure lifecycle events in your `MauiProgram.cs` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n    builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n    {\n#if ANDROID\n        events.AddAndroid(android => android\n            .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n            .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n        events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n            .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n    });\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to target each platform.\n- Android exposes `OnPause`, `OnStop`, `OnResume`, `OnCreate`, etc.\n- iOS exposes `DidEnterBackground`, `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate`, etc.\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` for the extension methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a58c239b-5316-45c6-813a-b6f26bf4dab3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":391,"requestId":"9543:18EC0:133DC60:15A7486:6A067051"},"id":"9153a79f-e989-490e-ba3a-d71979716db0","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:01:13.330Z","parentId":"337d02a3-cc7b-4716-9d4e-fd8a3c40a854"}
